This paper deals with data-intensive applications and proposes a data diffusion approach that combines dynamic resource provisioning, on-demand data replication and caching, and data locality-aware scheduling to achieve improved resource efficiency under varying workloads. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories such as Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Databases (cs.DB), Software Engineering (cs.SE), and Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE).
